  "description": "<p>Backcountry, frontside or backside, this ready-for-anything jacket has you covered. Waterproof-breathable shell has critically sealed seams to keep you dry and comfortable on wet slopeside days. When the mercury plummets, a generous supply of synthetic insulation keeps you warm without weighing you down. Backcountry-ready features include a powder skirt, RECCO reflector system and a helmet compatible hood.</p><ul><li>2-layer recycled nylon shell with MEC's VarioShell waterproof-breathable membrane and critically taped seams</li><li>Shell has a durable water repellency finish (DWR) that sheds snow and repels light rain</li><li>60g EcoSoft recycled synthetic insulation is warm and compressible</li><li>Recycled nylon lining glides over layers</li><li>Soft microfleece chin guard and collar keeps neck cozy when the hood is down</li><li>Helmet-compatible hood has an elasticized gusset to seal out drafts</li><li>Zipper pulls can be operated when wearing gloves</li><li>2 zippered handwarmer pockets, zippered chest pocket and hidden zippered pocket in right hand pocket</li><li>Velcro\u00ae cuff closures</li><li>Powder skirt snaps closed with an additional snap to keep it out of the way when not in use. Silicone gripper elastic keeps skirt in place</li><li>Built-in Recco\u00ae Rescue System reflector allows ski patrol and mountain rescue teams to detect and locate it</li></ul>",
